var book = {
	"name": "Ezra",
	"numChapters": 10,
	"chapters": {
		"1": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">1 </span>In the first year of Cyrus king of Persia, in order to fulfill the word of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> spoken by Jeremiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12018B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12018B\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> moved the heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12018C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12018C\"></sup> of Cyrus king of Persia to make a proclamation throughout his realm and also to put it in writing:",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>“This is what Cyrus king of Persia says:“‘The <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of heaven, has given me all the kingdoms of the earth and he has appointed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12019D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12019D\"></sup> me to build<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12019E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12019E\"></sup> a temple for him at Jerusalem in Judah.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Any of his people among you may go up to Jerusalem in Judah and build the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, the God who is in Jerusalem, and may their God be with them.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>And in any locality where survivors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12021F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12021F\"></sup> may now be living, the people are to provide them with silver and gold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12021G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12021G\"></sup> with goods and livestock, and with freewill offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12021H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12021H\"></sup> for the temple of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12021I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12021I\"></sup> in Jerusalem.’”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12021J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12021J\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then the family heads of Judah and Benjamin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12022K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12022K\"></sup> and the priests and Levites—everyone whose heart God had moved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12022L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12022L\"></sup>—prepared to go up and build the house<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12022M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12022M\"></sup> of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>All their neighbors assisted them with articles of silver and gold,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12023N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12023N\"></sup> with goods and livestock, and with valuable gifts, in addition to all the freewill offerings.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Moreover, King Cyrus brought out the articles belonging to the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, which Nebuchadnezzar had carried away from Jerusalem and had placed in the temple of his god.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12024O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12024O\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Cyrus king of Persia had them brought by Mithredath the treasurer, who counted them out to Sheshbazzar<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12025P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12025P\"></sup> the prince of Judah.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>This was the inventory:",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>In all, there were 5,400 articles of gold and of silver. Sheshbazzar brought all these along with the exiles when they came up from Babylon to Jerusalem."
		},
		"2": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">2 </span>Now these are the people of the province who came up from the captivity of the exiles,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12029B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12029B\"></sup> whom Nebuchadnezzar king of Babylon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12029C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12029C\"></sup> had taken captive to Babylon (they returned to Jerusalem and Judah, each to their own town,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12029D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12029D\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>in company with Zerubbabel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12030E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12030E\"></sup> Joshua,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12030F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12030F\"></sup> Nehemiah, Seraiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12030G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12030G\"></sup> Reelaiah, Mordecai, Bilshan, Mispar, Bigvai, Rehum and Baanah):The list of the men of the people of Israel:",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>The priests:",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>The Levites:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12068R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12068R\"></sup>",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>The musicians:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12069T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12069T\"></sup>",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>The gatekeepers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12070U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12070U\"></sup> of the temple:",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>The temple servants:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12071V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12071V\"></sup>",
			"55": "<sup class=\"versenum\">55 </sup>The descendants of the servants of Solomon:",
			"59": "<sup class=\"versenum\">59 </sup>The following came up from the towns of Tel Melah, Tel Harsha, Kerub, Addon and Immer, but they could not show that their families were descended<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12087X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12087X\"></sup> from Israel:",
			"61": "<sup class=\"versenum\">61 </sup>And from among the priests:",
			"62": "<sup class=\"versenum\">62 </sup>These searched for their family records, but they could not find them and so were excluded from the priesthood<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12090Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12090Z\"></sup> as unclean.",
			"63": "<sup class=\"versenum\">63 </sup>The governor ordered them not to eat any of the most sacred food<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12091AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12091AA\"></sup> until there was a priest ministering with the Urim and Thummim.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12091AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12091AB\"></sup>",
			"64": "<sup class=\"versenum\">64 </sup>The whole company numbered 42,360,",
			"65": "<sup class=\"versenum\">65 </sup>besides their 7,337 male and female slaves; and they also had 200 male and female singers.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12093AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12093AC\"></sup>",
			"66": "<sup class=\"versenum\">66 </sup>They had 736 horses,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12094AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12094AD\"></sup> 245 mules,",
			"67": "<sup class=\"versenum\">67 </sup>435 camels and 6,720 donkeys.",
			"68": "<sup class=\"versenum\">68 </sup>When they arrived at the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem, some of the heads of the families<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12096AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12096AE\"></sup> gave freewill offerings toward the rebuilding of the house of God on its site.",
			"69": "<sup class=\"versenum\">69 </sup>According to their ability they gave to the treasury for this work 61,000 darics of gold, 5,000 minas of silver and 100 priestly garments.",
			"70": "<sup class=\"versenum\">70 </sup>The priests, the Levites, the musicians, the gatekeepers and the temple servants settled in their own towns, along with some of the other people, and the rest of the Israelites settled in their towns.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12098AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12098AF\"></sup>"
		},
		"3": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">3 </span>When the seventh month came and the Israelites had settled in their towns,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12099A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12099A\"></sup> the people assembled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12099B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12099B\"></sup> together as one in Jerusalem.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Joshua<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12100C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12100C\"></sup> son of Jozadak<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12100D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12100D\"></sup> and his fellow priests and Zerubbabel son of Shealtiel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12100E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12100E\"></sup> and his associates began to build the altar of the God of Israel to sacrifice burnt offerings on it, in accordance with what is written in the Law of Moses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12100F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12100F\"></sup> the man of God.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Despite their fear<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12101G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12101G\"></sup> of the peoples around them, they built the altar on its foundation and sacrificed burnt offerings on it to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, both the morning and evening sacrifices.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12101H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12101H\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then in accordance with what is written, they celebrated the Festival of Tabernacles<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12102I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12102I\"></sup> with the required number of burnt offerings prescribed for each day.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>After that, they presented the regular burnt offerings, the New Moon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12103J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12103J\"></sup> sacrifices and the sacrifices for all the appointed sacred festivals of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12103K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12103K\"></sup> as well as those brought as freewill offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>On the first day of the seventh month they began to offer burnt offerings to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, though the foundation of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>’s temple had not yet been laid.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Then they gave money to the masons and carpenters,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12105L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12105L\"></sup> and gave food and drink and olive oil to the people of Sidon and Tyre, so that they would bring cedar logs<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12105M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12105M\"></sup> by sea from Lebanon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12105N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12105N\"></sup> to Joppa, as authorized by Cyrus<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12105O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12105O\"></sup> king of Persia.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>In the second month<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12106P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12106P\"></sup> of the second year after their arrival at the house of God in Jerusalem, Zerubbabel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12106Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12106Q\"></sup> son of Shealtiel, Joshua son of Jozadak and the rest of the people (the priests and the Levites and all who had returned from the captivity to Jerusalem) began the work. They appointed Levites twenty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12106R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12106R\"></sup> years old and older to supervise the building of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Joshua<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12107S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12107S\"></sup> and his sons and brothers and Kadmiel and his sons (descendants of Hodaviah) and the sons of Henadad and their sons and brothers—all Levites—joined together in supervising those working on the house of God.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>When the builders laid<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12108T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12108T\"></sup> the foundation of the temple of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the priests in their vestments and with trumpets,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12108U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12108U\"></sup> and the Levites (the sons of Asaph) with cymbals, took their places to praise<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12108V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12108V\"></sup> the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, as prescribed by David<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12108W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12108W\"></sup> king of Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12108X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12108X\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>With praise and thanksgiving they sang to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>:“He is good;his love toward Israel endures forever.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12109Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12109Y\"></sup>And all the people gave a great shout<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12109Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12109Z\"></sup> of praise to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, because the foundation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12109AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12109AA\"></sup> of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> was laid.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But many of the older priests and Levites and family heads, who had seen the former temple,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12110AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12110AB\"></sup> wept<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12110AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12110AC\"></sup> aloud when they saw the foundation of this temple being laid, while many others shouted for joy.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>No one could distinguish the sound of the shouts of joy<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12111AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12111AD\"></sup> from the sound of weeping, because the people made so much noise. And the sound was heard far away."
		},
		"4": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">4 </span>When the enemies of Judah and Benjamin heard that the exiles were building<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12112A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12112A\"></sup> a temple for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel,",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>they came to Zerubbabel and to the heads of the families and said, “Let us help you build because, like you, we seek your God and have been sacrificing to him since the time of Esarhaddon<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12113B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12113B\"></sup> king of Assyria, who brought us here.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12113C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12113C\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>But Zerubbabel, Joshua and the rest of the heads of the families of Israel answered, “You have no part with us in building a temple to our God. We alone will build it for the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, as King Cyrus, the king of Persia, commanded us.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12114D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12114D\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then the peoples around them set out to discourage the people of Judah and make them afraid to go on building.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12115E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12115E\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>They bribed officials to work against them and frustrate their plans during the entire reign of Cyrus king of Persia and down to the reign of Darius king of Persia.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>At the beginning of the reign of Xerxes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12117F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12117F\"></sup> they lodged an accusation against the people of Judah and Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12117G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12117G\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>And in the days of Artaxerxes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12118H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12118H\"></sup> king of Persia, Bishlam, Mithredath, Tabeel and the rest of his associates wrote a letter to Artaxerxes. The letter was written in Aramaic script and in the Aramaic<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12118I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12118I\"></sup> language.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Rehum the commanding officer and Shimshai the secretary wrote a letter against Jerusalem to Artaxerxes the king as follows:",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Rehum the commanding officer and Shimshai the secretary, together with the rest of their associates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12120J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12120J\"></sup>—the judges, officials and administrators over the people from Persia, Uruk<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12120K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12120K\"></sup> and Babylon, the Elamites of Susa,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12120L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12120L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>and the other people whom the great and honorable Ashurbanipal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12121M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12121M\"></sup> deported and settled in the city of Samaria and elsewhere in Trans-Euphrates.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12121N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12121N\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>(This is a copy of the letter they sent him.)To King Artaxerxes,From your servants in Trans-Euphrates:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The king should know that the people who came up to us from you have gone to Jerusalem and are rebuilding that rebellious and wicked city. They are restoring the walls and repairing the foundations.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12123O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12123O\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Furthermore, the king should know that if this city is built and its walls are restored, no more taxes, tribute or duty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12124P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12124P\"></sup> will be paid, and eventually the royal revenues will suffer.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Now since we are under obligation to the palace and it is not proper for us to see the king dishonored, we are sending this message to inform the king,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>so that a search may be made in the archives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12126Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12126Q\"></sup> of your predecessors. In these records you will find that this city is a rebellious city, troublesome to kings and provinces, a place with a long history of sedition. That is why this city was destroyed.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12126R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12126R\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>We inform the king that if this city is built and its walls are restored, you will be left with nothing in Trans-Euphrates.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>The king sent this reply:To Rehum the commanding officer, Shimshai the secretary and the rest of their associates living in Samaria and elsewhere in Trans-Euphrates:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12128S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12128S\"></sup>Greetings.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>The letter you sent us has been read and translated in my presence.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>I issued an order and a search was made, and it was found that this city has a long history of revolt<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12130T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12130T\"></sup> against kings and has been a place of rebellion and sedition.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>Jerusalem has had powerful kings ruling over the whole of Trans-Euphrates,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12131U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12131U\"></sup> and taxes, tribute and duty were paid to them.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now issue an order to these men to stop work, so that this city will not be rebuilt until I so order.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>Be careful not to neglect this matter. Why let this threat grow, to the detriment of the royal interests?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12133V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12133V\"></sup>",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>As soon as the copy of the letter of King Artaxerxes was read to Rehum and Shimshai the secretary and their associates,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12134W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12134W\"></sup> they went immediately to the Jews in Jerusalem and compelled them by force to stop.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Thus the work on the house of God in Jerusalem came to a standstill until the second year of the reign of Darius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12135X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12135X\"></sup> king of Persia."
		},
		"5": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">5 </span>Now Haggai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12136A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12136A\"></sup> the prophet and Zechariah<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12136B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12136B\"></sup> the prophet, a descendant of Iddo, prophesied<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12136C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12136C\"></sup> to the Jews in Judah and Jerusalem in the name of the God of Israel, who was over them.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Zerubbabel<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12137D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12137D\"></sup> son of Shealtiel and Joshua<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12137E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12137E\"></sup> son of Jozadak set to work<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12137F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12137F\"></sup> to rebuild the house of God in Jerusalem. And the prophets of God were with them, supporting them.",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>At that time Tattenai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12138G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12138G\"></sup> governor of Trans-Euphrates, and Shethar-Bozenai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12138H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12138H\"></sup> and their associates went to them and asked, “Who authorized you to rebuild this temple and to finish it?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12138I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12138I\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>They also asked, “What are the names of those who are constructing this building?”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>But the eye of their God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12140J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12140J\"></sup> was watching over the elders of the Jews, and they were not stopped until a report could go to Darius and his written reply be received.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>This is a copy of the letter that Tattenai, governor of Trans-Euphrates, and Shethar-Bozenai and their associates, the officials of Trans-Euphrates, sent to King Darius.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>The report they sent him read as follows:To King Darius:Cordial greetings.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>The king should know that we went to the district of Judah, to the temple of the great God. The people are building it with large stones and placing the timbers in the walls. The work<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12143K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12143K\"></sup> is being carried on with diligence and is making rapid progress under their direction.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>We questioned the elders and asked them, “Who authorized you to rebuild this temple and to finish it?”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12144L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12144L\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>We also asked them their names, so that we could write down the names of their leaders for your information.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>This is the answer they gave us:“We are the servants of the God of heaven and earth, and we are rebuilding the temple<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12146M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12146M\"></sup> that was built many years ago, one that a great king of Israel built and finished.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>But because our ancestors angered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12147N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12147N\"></sup> the God of heaven, he gave them into the hands of Nebuchadnezzar the Chaldean, king of Babylon, who destroyed this temple and deported the people to Babylon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12147O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12147O\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“However, in the first year of Cyrus king of Babylon, King Cyrus issued a decree<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12148P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12148P\"></sup> to rebuild this house of God.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>He even removed from the temple of Babylon the gold and silver articles of the house of God, which Nebuchadnezzar had taken from the temple in Jerusalem and brought to the temple in Babylon.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12149Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12149Q\"></sup> Then King Cyrus gave them to a man named Sheshbazzar,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12149R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12149R\"></sup> whom he had appointed governor,",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>and he told him, ‘Take these articles and go and deposit them in the temple in Jerusalem. And rebuild the house of God on its site.’",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>“So this Sheshbazzar came and laid the foundations of the house of God<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12151S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12151S\"></sup> in Jerusalem. From that day to the present it has been under construction but is not yet finished.”",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>Now if it pleases the king, let a search be made in the royal archives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12152T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12152T\"></sup> of Babylon to see if King Cyrus did in fact issue a decree to rebuild this house of God in Jerusalem. Then let the king send us his decision in this matter."
		},
		"6": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">6 </span>King Darius then issued an order, and they searched in the archives<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12153A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12153A\"></sup> stored in the treasury at Babylon.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>A scroll was found in the citadel of Ecbatana in the province of Media, and this was written on it:Memorandum:",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>In the first year of King Cyrus, the king issued a decree concerning the temple of God in Jerusalem:Let the temple be rebuilt as a place to present sacrifices, and let its foundations be laid.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12155B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12155B\"></sup> It is to be sixty cubits high and sixty cubits wide,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>with three courses<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12156C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12156C\"></sup> of large stones and one of timbers. The costs are to be paid by the royal treasury.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12156D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12156D\"></sup>",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Also, the gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12157E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12157E\"></sup> and silver articles of the house of God, which Nebuchadnezzar took from the temple in Jerusalem and brought to Babylon, are to be returned to their places in the temple in Jerusalem; they are to be deposited in the house of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12157F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12157F\"></sup>",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Now then, Tattenai,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12158G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12158G\"></sup> governor of Trans-Euphrates, and Shethar-Bozenai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12158H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12158H\"></sup> and you other officials of that province, stay away from there.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Do not interfere with the work on this temple of God. Let the governor of the Jews and the Jewish elders rebuild this house of God on its site.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Moreover, I hereby decree what you are to do for these elders of the Jews in the construction of this house of God:Their expenses are to be fully paid out of the royal treasury,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12160I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12160I\"></sup> from the revenues<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12160J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12160J\"></sup> of Trans-Euphrates, so that the work will not stop.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Whatever is needed—young bulls, rams, male lambs for burnt offerings<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12161K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12161K\"></sup> to the God of heaven, and wheat, salt, wine and olive oil, as requested by the priests in Jerusalem—must be given them daily without fail,",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>so that they may offer sacrifices pleasing to the God of heaven and pray for the well-being of the king and his sons.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12162L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12162L\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Furthermore, I decree that if anyone defies this edict, a beam is to be pulled from their house and they are to be impaled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12163M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12163M\"></sup> on it. And for this crime their house is to be made a pile of rubble.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12163N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12163N\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>May God, who has caused his Name to dwell there,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12164O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12164O\"></sup> overthrow any king or people who lifts a hand to change this decree or to destroy this temple in Jerusalem.I Darius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12164P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12164P\"></sup> have decreed it. Let it be carried out with diligence.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Then, because of the decree King Darius had sent, Tattenai, governor of Trans-Euphrates, and Shethar-Bozenai and their associates<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12165Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12165Q\"></sup> carried it out with diligence.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>So the elders of the Jews continued to build and prosper under the preaching<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12166R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12166R\"></sup> of Haggai the prophet and Zechariah, a descendant of Iddo. They finished building the temple according to the command of the God of Israel and the decrees of Cyrus,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12166S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12166S\"></sup> Darius<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12166T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12166T\"></sup> and Artaxerxes,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12166U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12166U\"></sup> kings of Persia.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>The temple was completed on the third day of the month Adar, in the sixth year of the reign of King Darius.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12167V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12167V\"></sup>",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>Then the people of Israel—the priests, the Levites and the rest of the exiles—celebrated the dedication<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12168W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12168W\"></sup> of the house of God with joy.",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>For the dedication of this house of God they offered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12169X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12169X\"></sup> a hundred bulls, two hundred rams, four hundred male lambs and, as a sin offering for all Israel, twelve male goats, one for each of the tribes of Israel.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>And they installed the priests in their divisions<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12170Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12170Y\"></sup> and the Levites in their groups<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12170Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12170Z\"></sup> for the service of God at Jerusalem, according to what is written in the Book of Moses.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12170AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12170AA\"></sup>",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>On the fourteenth day of the first month, the exiles celebrated the Passover.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12171AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12171AB\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>The priests and Levites had purified themselves and were all ceremonially clean. The Levites slaughtered<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12172AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12172AC\"></sup> the Passover lamb for all the exiles, for their relatives the priests and for themselves.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>So the Israelites who had returned from the exile ate it, together with all who had separated themselves<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12173AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12173AD\"></sup> from the unclean practices<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12173AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12173AE\"></sup> of their Gentile neighbors in order to seek the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12173AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12173AF\"></sup> the God of Israel.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>For seven days they celebrated with joy the Festival of Unleavened Bread,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12174AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12174AG\"></sup> because the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> had filled them with joy by changing the attitude<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12174AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12174AH\"></sup> of the king of Assyria so that he assisted them in the work on the house of God, the God of Israel."
		},
		"7": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">7 </span>After these things, during the reign of Artaxerxes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12175A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12175A\"></sup> king of Persia, Ezra son of Seraiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12175B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12175B\"></sup> the son of Azariah, the son of Hilkiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12175C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12175C\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>the son of Shallum, the son of Zadok,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12176D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12176D\"></sup> the son of Ahitub,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12176E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12176E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>the son of Amariah, the son of Azariah, the son of Meraioth,",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>the son of Zerahiah, the son of Uzzi, the son of Bukki,",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>the son of Abishua, the son of Phinehas,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12179F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12179F\"></sup> the son of Eleazar, the son of Aaron the chief priest—",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>this Ezra<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12180G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12180G\"></sup> came up from Babylon. He was a teacher well versed in the Law of Moses, which the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, had given. The king had granted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12180H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12180H\"></sup> him everything he asked, for the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> his God was on him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12180I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12180I\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>Some of the Israelites, including priests, Levites, musicians, gatekeepers and temple servants, also came up to Jerusalem in the seventh year of King Artaxerxes.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12181J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12181J\"></sup>",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Ezra arrived in Jerusalem in the fifth month of the seventh year of the king.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>He had begun his journey from Babylon on the first day of the first month, and he arrived in Jerusalem on the first day of the fifth month, for the gracious hand of his God was on him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12183K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12183K\"></sup>",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>For Ezra had devoted himself to the study and observance of the Law of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, and to teaching<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12184L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12184L\"></sup> its decrees and laws in Israel.",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>This is a copy of the letter King Artaxerxes had given to Ezra the priest, a teacher of the Law, a man learned in matters concerning the commands and decrees of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> for Israel:",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Artaxerxes, king of kings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12186M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12186M\"></sup>To Ezra the priest, teacher of the Law of the God of heaven:Greetings.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>Now I decree that any of the Israelites in my kingdom, including priests and Levites, who volunteer to go to Jerusalem with you, may go.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>You are sent by the king and his seven advisers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12188N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12188N\"></sup> to inquire about Judah and Jerusalem with regard to the Law of your God, which is in your hand.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Moreover, you are to take with you the silver and gold that the king and his advisers have freely given<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12189O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12189O\"></sup> to the God of Israel, whose dwelling<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12189P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12189P\"></sup> is in Jerusalem,",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>together with all the silver and gold<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12190Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12190Q\"></sup> you may obtain from the province of Babylon, as well as the freewill offerings of the people and priests for the temple of their God in Jerusalem.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12190R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12190R\"></sup>",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>With this money be sure to buy bulls, rams and male lambs,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12191S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12191S\"></sup> together with their grain offerings and drink offerings,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12191T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12191T\"></sup> and sacrifice<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12191U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12191U\"></sup> them on the altar of the temple of your God in Jerusalem.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>You and your fellow Israelites may then do whatever seems best with the rest of the silver and gold, in accordance with the will of your God.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>Deliver<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12193V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12193V\"></sup> to the God of Jerusalem all the articles entrusted to you for worship in the temple of your God.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>And anything else needed for the temple of your God that you are responsible to supply, you may provide from the royal treasury.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12194W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12194W\"></sup>",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>Now I, King Artaxerxes, decree that all the treasurers of Trans-Euphrates are to provide with diligence whatever Ezra the priest, the teacher of the Law of the God of heaven, may ask of you—",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>up to a hundred talents of silver, a hundred cors of wheat, a hundred baths of wine, a hundred baths of olive oil, and salt without limit.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Whatever the God of heaven has prescribed, let it be done with diligence for the temple of the God of heaven. Why should his wrath fall on the realm of the king and of his sons?<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12197X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12197X\"></sup>",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>You are also to know that you have no authority to impose taxes, tribute or duty<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12198Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12198Y\"></sup> on any of the priests, Levites, musicians, gatekeepers, temple servants or other workers at this house of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12198Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12198Z\"></sup>",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And you, Ezra, in accordance with the wisdom of your God, which you possess, appoint<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12199AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12199AA\"></sup> magistrates and judges to administer justice to all the people of Trans-Euphrates—all who know the laws of your God. And you are to teach<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12199AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12199AB\"></sup> any who do not know them.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>Whoever does not obey the law of your God and the law of the king must surely be punished by death, banishment, confiscation of property, or imprisonment.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12200AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12200AC\"></sup>",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>Praise be to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of our ancestors, who has put it into the king’s heart<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12201AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12201AD\"></sup> to bring honor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12201AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12201AE\"></sup> to the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem in this way",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>and who has extended his good favor<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12202AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12202AF\"></sup> to me before the king and his advisers and all the king’s powerful officials. Because the hand of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God was on me,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12202AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12202AG\"></sup> I took courage and gathered leaders from Israel to go up with me."
		},
		"8": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">8 </span>These are the family heads and those registered with them who came up with me from Babylon during the reign of King Artaxerxes:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12203A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12203A\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>of the descendants of Phinehas, Gershom;of the descendants of Ithamar, Daniel;of the descendants of David, Hattush",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>of the descendants of Shekaniah;<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12205B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12205B\"></sup>of the descendants of Parosh,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12205C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12205C\"></sup> Zechariah, and with him were registered 150 men;",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>of the descendants of Pahath-Moab,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12206D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12206D\"></sup> Eliehoenai son of Zerahiah, and with him 200 men;",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>of the descendants of Zattu, Shekaniah son of Jahaziel, and with him 300 men;",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>of the descendants of Adin,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12208E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12208E\"></sup> Ebed son of Jonathan, and with him 50 men;",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>of the descendants of Elam, Jeshaiah son of Athaliah, and with him 70 men;",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>of the descendants of Shephatiah, Zebadiah son of Michael, and with him 80 men;",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>of the descendants of Joab, Obadiah son of Jehiel, and with him 218 men;",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>of the descendants of Bani, Shelomith son of Josiphiah, and with him 160 men;",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>of the descendants of Bebai, Zechariah son of Bebai, and with him 28 men;",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>of the descendants of Azgad, Johanan son of Hakkatan, and with him 110 men;",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>of the descendants of Adonikam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12215F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12215F\"></sup> the last ones, whose names were Eliphelet, Jeuel and Shemaiah, and with them 60 men;",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>of the descendants of Bigvai, Uthai and Zakkur, and with them 70 men.",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>I assembled them at the canal that flows toward Ahava,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12217G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12217G\"></sup> and we camped there three days. When I checked among the people and the priests, I found no Levites<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12217H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12217H\"></sup> there.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So I summoned Eliezer, Ariel, Shemaiah, Elnathan, Jarib, Elnathan, Nathan, Zechariah and Meshullam, who were leaders, and Joiarib and Elnathan, who were men of learning,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and I ordered them to go to Iddo, the leader in Kasiphia. I told them what to say to Iddo and his fellow Levites, the temple servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12219I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12219I\"></sup> in Kasiphia, so that they might bring attendants to us for the house of our God.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Because the gracious hand of our God was on us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12220J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12220J\"></sup> they brought us Sherebiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12220K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12220K\"></sup> a capable man, from the descendants of Mahli son of Levi, the son of Israel, and Sherebiah’s sons and brothers, 18 in all;",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>and Hashabiah, together with Jeshaiah from the descendants of Merari, and his brothers and nephews, 20 in all.",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>They also brought 220 of the temple servants<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12222L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12222L\"></sup>—a body that David and the officials had established to assist the Levites. All were registered by name.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>There, by the Ahava Canal,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12223M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12223M\"></sup> I proclaimed a fast, so that we might humble ourselves before our God and ask him for a safe journey<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12223N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12223N\"></sup> for us and our children, with all our possessions.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>I was ashamed to ask the king for soldiers<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12224O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12224O\"></sup> and horsemen to protect us from enemies on the road, because we had told the king, “The gracious hand of our God is on everyone<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12224P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12224P\"></sup> who looks to him, but his great anger is against all who forsake him.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12224Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12224Q\"></sup>”",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>So we fasted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12225R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12225R\"></sup> and petitioned our God about this, and he answered our prayer.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>Then I set apart twelve of the leading priests, namely, Sherebiah,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12226S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12226S\"></sup> Hashabiah and ten of their brothers,",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>and I weighed out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12227T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12227T\"></sup> to them the offering of silver and gold and the articles that the king, his advisers, his officials and all Israel present there had donated for the house of our God.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>I weighed out to them 650 talents of silver, silver articles weighing 100 talents, 100 talents of gold,",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>20 bowls of gold valued at 1,000 darics, and two fine articles of polished bronze, as precious as gold.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>I said to them, “You as well as these articles are consecrated to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12230U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12230U\"></sup> The silver and gold are a freewill offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your ancestors.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>Guard them carefully until you weigh them out in the chambers of the house of the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> in Jerusalem before the leading priests and the Levites and the family heads of Israel.”",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>Then the priests and Levites received the silver and gold and sacred articles that had been weighed out to be taken to the house of our God in Jerusalem.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>On the twelfth day of the first month we set out from the Ahava Canal<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12233V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12233V\"></sup> to go to Jerusalem. The hand of our God was on us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12233W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12233W\"></sup> and he protected us from enemies and bandits along the way.",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>So we arrived in Jerusalem, where we rested three days.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12234X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12234X\"></sup>",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>On the fourth day, in the house of our God, we weighed out<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12235Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12235Y\"></sup> the silver and gold and the sacred articles into the hands of Meremoth<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12235Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12235Z\"></sup> son of Uriah, the priest. Eleazar son of Phinehas was with him, and so were the Levites Jozabad<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12235AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12235AA\"></sup> son of Jeshua and Noadiah son of Binnui.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12235AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12235AB\"></sup>",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>Everything was accounted for by number and weight, and the entire weight was recorded at that time.",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Then the exiles who had returned from captivity sacrificed burnt offerings to the God of Israel: twelve bulls<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12237AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12237AC\"></sup> for all Israel,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12237AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12237AD\"></sup> ninety-six rams, seventy-seven male lambs and, as a sin offering, twelve male goats.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12237AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12237AE\"></sup> All this was a burnt offering to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>.",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>They also delivered the king’s orders<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12238AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12238AF\"></sup> to the royal satraps and to the governors of Trans-Euphrates,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12238AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12238AG\"></sup> who then gave assistance to the people and to the house of God.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12238AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12238AH\"></sup>"
		},
		"9": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">9 </span>After these things had been done, the leaders came to me and said, “The people of Israel, including the priests and the Levites, have not kept themselves separate<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12239A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12239A\"></sup> from the neighboring peoples with their detestable practices, like those of the Canaanites, Hittites, Perizzites, Jebusites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12239B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12239B\"></sup> Ammonites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12239C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12239C\"></sup> Moabites,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12239D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12239D\"></sup> Egyptians and Amorites.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12239E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12239E\"></sup>",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>They have taken some of their daughters<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12240F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12240F\"></sup> as wives for themselves and their sons, and have mingled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12240G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12240G\"></sup> the holy race<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12240H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12240H\"></sup> with the peoples around them. And the leaders and officials have led the way in this unfaithfulness.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12240I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12240I\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>When I heard this, I tore<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12241J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12241J\"></sup> my tunic and cloak, pulled hair from my head and beard and sat down appalled.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12241K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12241K\"></sup>",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Then everyone who trembled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12242L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12242L\"></sup> at the words of the God of Israel gathered around me because of this unfaithfulness of the exiles. And I sat there appalled<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12242M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12242M\"></sup> until the evening sacrifice.",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>Then, at the evening sacrifice,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12243N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12243N\"></sup> I rose from my self-abasement, with my tunic and cloak torn, and fell on my knees with my hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12243O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12243O\"></sup> spread out to the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> my God",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>and prayed:“I am too ashamed<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12244P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12244P\"></sup> and disgraced, my God, to lift up my face to you, because our sins are higher than our heads and our guilt has reached to the heavens.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12244Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12244Q\"></sup>",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>From the days of our ancestors<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12245R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12245R\"></sup> until now, our guilt has been great. Because of our sins, we and our kings and our priests have been subjected to the sword<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12245S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12245S\"></sup> and captivity,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12245T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12245T\"></sup> to pillage and humiliation<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12245U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12245U\"></sup> at the hand of foreign kings, as it is today.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>“But now, for a brief moment, the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span> our God has been gracious<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12246V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12246V\"></sup> in leaving us a remnant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12246W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12246W\"></sup> and giving us a firm place<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12246X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12246X\"></sup> in his sanctuary, and so our God gives light to our eyes<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12246Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12246Y\"></sup> and a little relief in our bondage.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Though we are slaves,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12247Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12247Z\"></sup> our God has not forsaken us in our bondage. He has shown us kindness<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12247AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12247AA\"></sup> in the sight of the kings of Persia: He has granted us new life to rebuild the house of our God and repair its ruins,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12247AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12247AB\"></sup> and he has given us a wall of protection in Judah and Jerusalem.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>“But now, our God, what can we say after this? For we have forsaken the commands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12248AC&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AC&quot;&gt;AC&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12248AC\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>you gave through your servants the prophets when you said: ‘The land you are entering<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12249AD&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AD&quot;&gt;AD&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12249AD\"></sup> to possess is a land polluted<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12249AE&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AE&quot;&gt;AE&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12249AE\"></sup> by the corruption of its peoples. By their detestable practices<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12249AF&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AF&quot;&gt;AF&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12249AF\"></sup> they have filled it with their impurity from one end to the other.",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>Therefore, do not give your daughters in marriage to their sons or take their daughters for your sons. Do not seek a treaty of friendship with them<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12250AG&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AG&quot;&gt;AG&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12250AG\"></sup> at any time, that you may be strong<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12250AH&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AH&quot;&gt;AH&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12250AH\"></sup> and eat the good things<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12250AI&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AI&quot;&gt;AI&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12250AI\"></sup> of the land and leave it to your children as an everlasting inheritance.’<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12250AJ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AJ&quot;&gt;AJ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12250AJ\"></sup>",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>“What has happened to us is a result of our evil<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12251AK&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AK&quot;&gt;AK&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12251AK\"></sup> deeds and our great guilt, and yet, our God, you have punished us less than our sins deserved<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12251AL&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AL&quot;&gt;AL&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12251AL\"></sup> and have given us a remnant like this.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Shall we then break your commands again and intermarry<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12252AM&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AM&quot;&gt;AM&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12252AM\"></sup> with the peoples who commit such detestable practices? Would you not be angry enough with us to destroy us,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12252AN&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AN&quot;&gt;AN&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12252AN\"></sup> leaving us no remnant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12252AO&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AO&quot;&gt;AO&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12252AO\"></sup> or survivor?",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup><span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of Israel, you are righteous!<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12253AP&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AP&quot;&gt;AP&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12253AP\"></sup> We are left this day as a remnant. Here we are before you in our guilt, though because of it not one of us can stand<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12253AQ&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AQ&quot;&gt;AQ&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12253AQ\"></sup> in your presence.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12253AR&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AR&quot;&gt;AR&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12253AR\"></sup>”"
		},
		"10": {
			"1": "<span class=\"chapternum\">10 </span>While Ezra was praying and confessing,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12254A&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference A&quot;&gt;A&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12254A\"></sup> weeping<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12254B&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference B&quot;&gt;B&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12254B\"></sup> and throwing himself down before the house of God, a large crowd of Israelites—men, women and children—gathered around him. They too wept bitterly.",
			"2": "<sup class=\"versenum\">2 </sup>Then Shekaniah son of Jehiel, one of the descendants of Elam,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12255C&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference C&quot;&gt;C&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12255C\"></sup> said to Ezra, “We have been unfaithful<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12255D&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference D&quot;&gt;D&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12255D\"></sup> to our God by marrying foreign women from the peoples around us. But in spite of this, there is still hope for Israel.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12255E&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference E&quot;&gt;E&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12255E\"></sup>",
			"3": "<sup class=\"versenum\">3 </sup>Now let us make a covenant<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12256F&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference F&quot;&gt;F&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12256F\"></sup> before our God to send away<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12256G&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference G&quot;&gt;G&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12256G\"></sup> all these women and their children, in accordance with the counsel of my lord and of those who fear the commands of our God. Let it be done according to the Law.",
			"4": "<sup class=\"versenum\">4 </sup>Rise up; this matter is in your hands. We will support you, so take courage and do it.”",
			"5": "<sup class=\"versenum\">5 </sup>So Ezra rose up and put the leading priests and Levites and all Israel under oath<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12258H&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference H&quot;&gt;H&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12258H\"></sup> to do what had been suggested. And they took the oath.",
			"6": "<sup class=\"versenum\">6 </sup>Then Ezra withdrew from before the house of God and went to the room of Jehohanan son of Eliashib. While he was there, he ate no food and drank no water,<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12259I&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference I&quot;&gt;I&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12259I\"></sup> because he continued to mourn over the unfaithfulness of the exiles.",
			"7": "<sup class=\"versenum\">7 </sup>A proclamation was then issued throughout Judah and Jerusalem for all the exiles to assemble in Jerusalem.",
			"8": "<sup class=\"versenum\">8 </sup>Anyone who failed to appear within three days would forfeit all his property, in accordance with the decision of the officials and elders, and would himself be expelled from the assembly of the exiles.",
			"9": "<sup class=\"versenum\">9 </sup>Within the three days, all the men of Judah and Benjamin<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12262J&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference J&quot;&gt;J&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12262J\"></sup> had gathered in Jerusalem. And on the twentieth day of the ninth month, all the people were sitting in the square before the house of God, greatly distressed by the occasion and because of the rain.",
			"10": "<sup class=\"versenum\">10 </sup>Then Ezra<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12263K&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference K&quot;&gt;K&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12263K\"></sup> the priest stood up and said to them, “You have been unfaithful; you have married foreign women, adding to Israel’s guilt.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12263L&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference L&quot;&gt;L&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12263L\"></sup>",
			"11": "<sup class=\"versenum\">11 </sup>Now honor the <span style=\"font-variant: small-caps\" class=\"small-caps\">Lord</span>, the God of your ancestors, and do his will. Separate yourselves from the peoples around you and from your foreign wives.”<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12264M&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference M&quot;&gt;M&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12264M\"></sup>",
			"12": "<sup class=\"versenum\">12 </sup>The whole assembly responded with a loud voice:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12265N&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference N&quot;&gt;N&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12265N\"></sup> “You are right! We must do as you say.",
			"13": "<sup class=\"versenum\">13 </sup>But there are many people here and it is the rainy season; so we cannot stand outside. Besides, this matter cannot be taken care of in a day or two, because we have sinned greatly in this thing.",
			"14": "<sup class=\"versenum\">14 </sup>Let our officials act for the whole assembly. Then let everyone in our towns who has married a foreign woman come at a set time, along with the elders and judges<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12267O&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference O&quot;&gt;O&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12267O\"></sup> of each town, until the fierce anger<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12267P&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference P&quot;&gt;P&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12267P\"></sup> of our God in this matter is turned away from us.”",
			"15": "<sup class=\"versenum\">15 </sup>Only Jonathan son of Asahel and Jahzeiah son of Tikvah, supported by Meshullam and Shabbethai<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12268Q&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Q&quot;&gt;Q&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12268Q\"></sup> the Levite, opposed this.",
			"16": "<sup class=\"versenum\">16 </sup>So the exiles did as was proposed. Ezra the priest selected men who were family heads, one from each family division, and all of them designated by name. On the first day of the tenth month they sat down to investigate the cases,",
			"17": "<sup class=\"versenum\">17 </sup>and by the first day of the first month they finished dealing with all the men who had married foreign women.",
			"18": "<sup class=\"versenum\">18 </sup>Among the descendants of the priests, the following had married foreign women:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12271R&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference R&quot;&gt;R&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12271R\"></sup>From the descendants of Joshua<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12271S&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference S&quot;&gt;S&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12271S\"></sup> son of Jozadak, and his brothers: Maaseiah, Eliezer, Jarib and Gedaliah.",
			"19": "<sup class=\"versenum\">19 </sup>(They all gave their hands<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12272T&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference T&quot;&gt;T&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12272T\"></sup> in pledge to put away their wives, and for their guilt they each presented a ram from the flock as a guilt offering.)<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12272U&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference U&quot;&gt;U&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12272U\"></sup>",
			"20": "<sup class=\"versenum\">20 </sup>From the descendants of Immer:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12273V&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference V&quot;&gt;V&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12273V\"></sup>Hanani and Zebadiah.",
			"21": "<sup class=\"versenum\">21 </sup>From the descendants of Harim:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12274W&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference W&quot;&gt;W&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12274W\"></sup>Maaseiah, Elijah, Shemaiah, Jehiel and Uzziah.",
			"22": "<sup class=\"versenum\">22 </sup>From the descendants of Pashhur:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12275X&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference X&quot;&gt;X&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12275X\"></sup>Elioenai, Maaseiah, Ishmael, Nethanel, Jozabad and Elasah.",
			"23": "<sup class=\"versenum\">23 </sup>Among the Levites:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12276Y&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Y&quot;&gt;Y&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12276Y\"></sup>Jozabad, Shimei, Kelaiah (that is, Kelita), Pethahiah, Judah and Eliezer.",
			"24": "<sup class=\"versenum\">24 </sup>From the musicians:Eliashib.<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12277Z&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference Z&quot;&gt;Z&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12277Z\"></sup>From the gatekeepers:Shallum, Telem and Uri.",
			"25": "<sup class=\"versenum\">25 </sup>And among the other Israelites:From the descendants of Parosh:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12278AA&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AA&quot;&gt;AA&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12278AA\"></sup>Ramiah, Izziah, Malkijah, Mijamin, Eleazar, Malkijah and Benaiah.",
			"26": "<sup class=\"versenum\">26 </sup>From the descendants of Elam:<sup class=\"crossreference\" data-link=\"(&lt;a href=&quot;#cen-NIV-12279AB&quot; title=&quot;See cross-reference AB&quot;&gt;AB&lt;/a&gt;)\" data-cr=\"#cen-NIV-12279AB\"></sup>Mattaniah, Zechariah, Jehiel, Abdi, Jeremoth and Elijah.",
			"27": "<sup class=\"versenum\">27 </sup>From the descendants of Zattu:Elioenai, Eliashib, Mattaniah, Jeremoth, Zabad and Aziza.",
			"28": "<sup class=\"versenum\">28 </sup>From the descendants of Bebai:Jehohanan, Hananiah, Zabbai and Athlai.",
			"29": "<sup class=\"versenum\">29 </sup>From the descendants of Bani:Meshullam, Malluk, Adaiah, Jashub, Sheal and Jeremoth.",
			"30": "<sup class=\"versenum\">30 </sup>From the descendants of Pahath-Moab:Adna, Kelal, Benaiah, Maaseiah, Mattaniah, Bezalel, Binnui and Manasseh.",
			"31": "<sup class=\"versenum\">31 </sup>From the descendants of Harim:Eliezer, Ishijah, Malkijah, Shemaiah, Shimeon,",
			"32": "<sup class=\"versenum\">32 </sup>Benjamin, Malluk and Shemariah.",
			"33": "<sup class=\"versenum\">33 </sup>From the descendants of Hashum:Mattenai, Mattattah, Zabad, Eliphelet, Jeremai, Manasseh and Shimei.",
			"34": "<sup class=\"versenum\">34 </sup>From the descendants of Bani:Maadai, Amram, Uel,",
			"35": "<sup class=\"versenum\">35 </sup>Benaiah, Bedeiah, Keluhi,",
			"36": "<sup class=\"versenum\">36 </sup>Vaniah, Meremoth, Eliashib,",
			"37": "<sup class=\"versenum\">37 </sup>Mattaniah, Mattenai and Jaasu.",
			"38": "<sup class=\"versenum\">38 </sup>From the descendants of Binnui:Shimei,",
			"39": "<sup class=\"versenum\">39 </sup>Shelemiah, Nathan, Adaiah,",
			"40": "<sup class=\"versenum\">40 </sup>Maknadebai, Shashai, Sharai,",
			"41": "<sup class=\"versenum\">41 </sup>Azarel, Shelemiah, Shemariah,",
			"42": "<sup class=\"versenum\">42 </sup>Shallum, Amariah and Joseph.",
			"43": "<sup class=\"versenum\">43 </sup>From the descendants of Nebo:Jeiel, Mattithiah, Zabad, Zebina, Jaddai, Joel and Benaiah.",
			"44": "<sup class=\"versenum\">44 </sup>All these had married foreign women, and some of them had children by these wives."
		}
	}
};
